			<div class="content" id="post-content-1236750">
									

<p>Okay, so.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It is currently believed that there could be hundreds, if not thousands, of SCP-870 in the world. They are a clear and present danger to the public, and steps must be taken to destroy or contain the species.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>AND YET, <em>somehow</em>, It's Euclid, not Keter.</p>
<p>Standard practice is not to include drawings of SCPs, but then, I guess that's the point? The 5 year old's drawing doesn't seem like something the foundation would bother with.</p>
<p>Aside from that, it's not very interesting.</p>
<p>My initial reaction was kind of &quot;Uugh&#8230;&quot; but in retrospect it's not bad. Being perceived only by schizophrenics is interesting, I suppose? The statements that it is incredibly hostile seem like they're trying to play into cheap scares. The very last paragraph is pretty blatant in the &quot;THIS THING IS DANGEROUS, BE FUCKING SCARED. IT COULD BE SNEAKING UP ON YOU <em>RIGHT NOW!</em>&quot;</p>

							</div>

								
